Title: General Low Energy Dynamics of Supersymmetric Monopoles
Authors: Jerome P. Gauntlett, Chanju Kim, Kimyeong Lee, Piljin Yi
Comments: LaTeX, 36pages, typos fixed
Report-no: QMW-PH-00-06, KIAS-P00048
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D63 (2001) 065020
\\
  We derive general low energy dynamics of monopoles and dyons in N=2 and N=4
supersymmetric Yang-Mills theories by utilising a collective coordinate
expansion. The resulting new kind of supersymmetric quantum mechanics
incorporates the effects of multiple Higgs fields, both in the N=2 vector
multiplet and hypermultiplets, having non-vanishing expectation values.
